  "summary": "TPC-H (SF10) is an OLAP workload dominated by fact table scans (lineitem 60M, orders 15M) with selective range filters, complex multi-table joins, and aggregations. Bottlenecks: Q1 (60M scan with aggregation), Q3/Q5 (multi-way joins + partial agg), correlated subqueries (Q2, Q20-22). Critical optimizations: (1) Parallel morsel-driven scans (64 cores, L3 44MB → ~170K row morsels), (2) Hash indexes on join keys + zone maps on date columns, (3) Subquery decorrelation → semi-joins, (4) SIMD filtering for discount/quantity predicates, (5) Partial aggregation with thread-local hash tables + global merge. Storage: columnar layout for fact tables, compression on low-cardinality strings (flags, segments)."
